oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Vitamins, Antibiotics, Hormones and Enzymes
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Adams, C. R.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: supplemental vitamins
nutrition
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: It is generally accepted that vitamins A and E are essential nutrients for all species of animals. However, differences of opinion do exist as to the conditions under which supplemental vitamins A and E are required and at what levels they should be fed.
